      <strong>BITCOIN RISK INFORMATION</strong>: Bitcoin and other cryptocurrencies are a digital representation of value that function as a medium of exchange, a unit of account, or a store of value, but they do not have legal tender status in the United States. Cryptocurrencies are sometimes exchanged for U.S. dollars or other currencies around the world, but they are not generally backed or supported by any government or central bank.
